highlights:
• As of July 24th, there are 46 new confirmed cases of COVID-19, bringing the total to 49,656 reported cases.
  • The new cases are located in the Far North West (6), Far North Central (2), Far North East (10), North West (3), North Central (4), North East (1), Saskatoon (7), Regina (9), and South East (1) zones and three (3) cases have pending residence information.
  • Two (2) cases were SK residents tested out-of-province and were added to the case counts in the North Central (from July 23 (2)) zone.
  • 49,656 cases are confirmed
    • 12,192 cases are from the Regina area
    • 11,719 cases are from the Saskatoon area
    • 10,925 cases are from the North area (4,755 North West, 4,558 North Central, 1,612 North East)
    • 5,828 cases are from the South area (1,138 South West, 1,918 South Central, 2,772 South East)
    • 5,587 cases are from the Far North area (2,809 Far North West, 387 Far North Central, 2,391 Far North East)
    • 3,259 cases are from the Central area (833 Central West, 2,426 Central East)
    • 146 cases have pending residence information
  • 340 cases are considered active and 48,738 cases are considered recovered.
  • 12,810 of the cases are individuals in the 19 and under age category; all others are adults, with 50.1% of the cases males and 49.6% females.
  • 4% (1,817) of cases are travel-related, 61% (30,470) are contacts to known cases or involved in mass gathering(s), 27% (13,259) have no known exposures and 8% (4,110) are under investigation by local public health.
  • 2,549 cases are healthcare workers, although the source of their infections may not be health care related.
  • As of July 24th, a total of 63 individuals are hospitalized; including 52 inpatient hospitalizations and 11 ICU hospitalizations.
  • One (1) new death reported today. 578 Saskatchewan residents with COVID-19 have died with a case fatality rate of 1.2%.
  • 952,155 COVID-19 tests have been performed in the province. As of July 22nd, 2021 when other provincial and national numbers are available from PHAC, Saskatchewan’s per capita rate was 802,405 tests performed per million.  The national rate of 1,002,790 tests performed per million.
  • The 7-day average of new COVID-19 case number was 36 (3.0 new cases per 100,000).
